
1) What is a Java package?

a folder that groups similar classes together

2) What is the CLASSPATH variable all about?

if your package is not within the root folder of the java project, you can access it only by adding its directory to the classpath

3) What does the package structure mirror?

folder hierarchy from the root of the project

4 How do packages affect access to Java classes?

default or private access modifiers for example allow classes in the same package to access each other

5) What is an interface?

a template for classes to implement

6) What makes interfaces unique?

their methods and variables are all empty

7) What keyword is used to specify that a class is going to use a separate interface?

implements

8) What makes interfaces so useful?

they provide guidance on how to create classes that can then work together easily (having the same method/variable names)

9) What was added in JDK 8 that makes interfaces even more useful?

The default method which doesn't have to be overridden.

10) How many interfaces can a single class implement?

a lot